Dr Doreen Lugaliki 

The 39-year-old obstetrician had since March worked hard to keep Coronavirus patients alive at Nairobi South Hospital when she caught the dreaded disease. 

On July 10, 2020 Dr Lugaliki became the first Kenyan doctor to succumb to Coronavirus, just eight days after she first exhibited symptoms. 

Dr Lugaliki’s siblings checked her into Aga Khan Hospital after she started feeling unwell. 



