Much like Dr Lugaliki, Dr Stephen Mogusu spent his last days on earth caring for Coronavirus patients. 

He was the 13th doctor to succumb to Coronavirus. 

His unfortunate demise, however, brought into sharp focus the horrible treatment that some health workers have undergone while caring for patients. 

At Machakos County Hospital, a 28-year-old Dr Mogusu was caring for Coronavirus patients, many times without basic protective equipment. He had worked for five months, and had barely 30 days left on his contract. 

Just a few hours before the virus claimed his life on December 9, Dr Mogusu warned his colleagues in a Whatsapp group to push for their pay or get out of the profession with their health intact, while they still can. 

The health worker had not been paid for five months. He could not afford to buy diapers for his five-month-old daughter. Gire Ali 

A few days after the government banned all flights from China to curb the spread of Coronavirus, Kenya Airways security officer spotted a Southern Airlines plane landing at the Jomo Kenyatta International Airport. 

The direct flight from Guangzhou was ferrying 239 passengers into Kenya on February 26 and Mr Ali caught the touchdown on camera, before sharing it. 



