}




Transport CS James Macharia was angry, and branded Mr Ali a criminal for filming a security installation. 

But Kenyans, including Members of Parliament, differed, insisting that Mr Ali is a hero. 






Suspended Kenya Airways (KQ) employee Gire Ali reacts during an interview on February 28, 2020. PHOTO | JEFF ANGOTE | NATION MEDIA GROUP

 

His employer suspended him, and Mr Gire started receiving death threats via mobile phone. 

Public outrage and pressure from lawmakers saw Kenya Airways reinstate Mr Gire. 

The High Court issued orders barring the Director of Public Prosecutions from pursuing him in court, and police undertook not to arrest the whistleblower. Michael Olunga 

For the last eight years, Michael Olunga’s star has been rising, and he is now one of the top rated “little-known” strikers that starred in 2020 as per the world governing body, FIFA. 

He is only the third African to top the scoring charts in Japan’s top flight. 



