Only Cameroon’s Patrick Mboma (25 goals for Gamba Osaka in 1999) and Nigeria’s Peter Utaka (19 goals for Sanfrecce Hiroshima in 2016) have achieved the fete. 






Kashiwa Reysol's Kenyan striker Michael Olunga (left) receives his J-League Golden Boot Award on December 22, 2020.
Photo credit: J League | 

 

“Engineer” Olunga is the first African footballer to bag the most valuable player award in Japan’s J-League history. 

Mr Olunga scored 28 league goals in 32 games, leading newly promoted Kashiwa Reysol to seventh place in the J-League this year. 

The striker has previously played for Liberty Academy, Tusker FC, Gor Mahia, Djugardens (Sweden), Guizhou Zhicheng (China) and Girona (Spain, on loan). 



