Chief Justice David Maraga asked President Kenyatta to dissolve Parliament over its failure to enact the two-thirds gender rule law.
Photo credit: Sila Kiplagat | Nation Media Group

 

Even when President Kenyatta’s administration slashed the Judiciary’s budget, Justice Maraga did not budge. 

Justice Maraga and President Kenyatta have snubbed many each other’s events, and the former’s last State of the Judiciary address was no different. 

In his farewell speech, Justice Maraga insisted that he holds no grudges against President Kenyatta despite the incessant fights between the two. 

The Chief Justice is on terminal leave pending retirement on January 12, 2021. 



