Jane Kimiti 

Othaya Girls School Principal Ms Jane Kimiti loves integrating information technology in the education process. She also fights hard for girl-child empowerment. 

Her efforts may not have caught the attention of many outside stakeholders at the learning institution. 

But they were more than enough to convince the African Union to award her its continental teacher of the year award for 2020. 

Ms Kimiti is the third Kenyan teacher to get global recognition in three years for going above and beyond to improve the education experience for learners. 

Keriko Mixed Day Secondary School teacher Peter Tabichi was awarded the coveted Global Teacher Prize in 2019. 

In the same year Asumbi Girls mathematics teacher Erick Ademba was awarded the Continental Teacher Prize. Sisters caution politicians against using their brother’s death to push their selfish interests. Healthcare workers have had no option but to fund-raise for their infected colleagues. According to family members, the deceased was attached to the DP’s security detail for several years. The footbridge was damaged by a trailer carrying an excavator earlier in December 2020.